        <div class='post__title__excerpt wysiwyg p italic mb1 mt025 pr2 o4 theme__text ' >
            A decade after the discovery of the “amplituhedron,” physicists have excavated more of the timeless geometry underlying the standard picture of how particles move.        </div>
